<br>
1.  Rogue states like Iraq and North Korea can develop weapons of mass destruction but not deliver them.<br>
<br>
2.  Terrorist organizations like Al Qaida can deliver weapons of mass destruction but not develop them.<br>
<br>
3.  A terrorist organization working with the dictator of a rogue state can develop and deliver weapons of mass destruction anywhere in the world with impunity.<br>
<br>
If we don't stop 3. from happening, we're going to have total chaos in a few years.  You can kiss your world peace and your rights goodbye forever as whatever's left of the USA tries to piece together some sort of survival plan that doesn't blow up the whole planet.  We won't be worried about Iraqi civilians then, we'll be worrying about who to nuke next to stay alive until tomorrow.<br>
<br>
If you have a way to prevent 3. other than war on Iraq, let us know what it is already.  All I'm hearing from the anti-war crowd is &quot;Bush is BAD, Republicans are BAD, Americans are BAD&quot;, I'm not hearing any alternatives, and singing Kumbaya around the campfire doesn't cut it. <p>Zolina the Wind Caller, Forest Stalker of Healers United, Quellious<br>
